<subSubSection lastPageId="68" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="67" pageNumber="125" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="67.[1396,2605,3121,3282]" lastBlockId="68.[779,1373,281,710]" lastPageId="68" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="67" pageNumber="125">
<taxonomicName box="[1397,1545,3161,3194]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Desmalopex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="125" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Desmalopex</taxonomicName>
has been under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brisson" authorityYear="1762" box="[1779,1885,3161,3194]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Pteropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="125" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pteropus</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym since K. Andersen in 1912. Recent phylogenies demonstrated that it is a valid genus more closely related to monkeyfaced bats than typical pteropodines such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brisson" authorityYear="1762" box="[2016,2123,3243,3272]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Pteropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="125" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pteropus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[2137,2429,3243,3272]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Desmalopex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="125" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucopterus">Desmalopex leucopterus</taxonomicName>
is present in its typical form in the Luzon faunal region (Luzon and 
<collectingRegion box="[967,1148,326,355]" country="Philippines" name="Catanduanes" pageId="68" pageNumber="126">Catanduanes</collectingRegion>
islands); other specimens referred might represent an undescribed species in the Mindanao faunal region (on 
<collectingRegion box="[940,1050,439,472]" country="Philippines" name="Dinagat Islands" pageId="68" pageNumber="126">Dinagat</collectingRegion>
Island). Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
